name: Marcus Lee

research.notes: Spoke at TechCrunch Disrupt 2023, ongoing funding discussions

long_summary: Marcus Lee founded CloudVoyager in 2019 with a vision to simplify cloud orchestration. Under his leadership the company grew from a two-person team to over 50 employees in five years. He has negotiated partnerships with major cloud providers and secured Series A and B funding rounds totaling $30M. Marcus is a frequent speaker at industry events and mentors early-stage founders through accelerator programs. He holds a BS in Computer Science from the University of Texas at Austin. His strategic insight and passion for developer experience have driven CloudVoyagerâ€™s adoption by Fortune 500 clients.
